<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="311" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1737.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Johnson</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]<note n="10" xml:id="d311fn10">This
                                    despatch No. 193 is printed in full under Political Affairs,
                                        <ref target="#pg_292">p. 292</ref>; the translation of the
                                    reply here referred to is there shown as inclosure
                                2.</note></seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 193.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 189 dated
                            July 22, 1915, I have the honor to enclose * * * copy and translation of
                            the reply to my note of protest against the diversion of funds, copy of
                            which I enclosed in the despatch referred to above. * * *</p>
                        <p>As for the statement in the Dominican Government’s note that the budget
                            has not been exceeded, it is in contradiction of what the President
                            himself had said to me on two occasions, and at best is technically true
                            only; for example, the entire credit provided in the budget for the
                            fiscal year from July 1, 1915, to June 30, 1916, may not yet have been
                            exceeded.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart Johnson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>